  "summary": "Permissions must be enforced before retrieval.",
  "body": "Permissions must be enforced before retrieval.\n\nThe system first authenticates the user, resolves source-system permissions, applies metadata and ACL filters, retrieves only authorized content, reranks results, and then provides permitted context to the LLM.\n\nUnauthorized information must never enter the LLM context window.\n\nACLs should be inherited from source systems whenever possible and all retrieval operations should be auditable.",
